{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0143NjdmxRiC4bLgRR7kuLwF","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: \"PRD-549.6\"\n3\ttitle: \"Move push_branch to its own submodule with colocated tests\"\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: ready\n6\tpriority: medium\n7\teffort: xs\n8\tcapability: trivial\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-549-builtins-package-split]]\"\n10\tdepends_on:\n11\t  - \"[[PRD-549.1-pytest-config-wheel-conftest]]\"\n12\t  - \"[[PRD-549.2-scaffold-builtins-package]]\"\n13\tblocks:\n14\t  - \"[[PRD-549.12-final-cleanup]]\"\n15\timpacts:\n16\t  - src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch.py\n17\t  - src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch_test.py\n18\t  - src/darkfactory/builtins/__init__.py\n19\tworkflow: null\n20\ttarget_version: null\n21\tcreated: 2026-04-08\n22\tupdated: 2026-04-08\n23\ttags:\n24\t  - refactor\n25\t  - tests\n26\t  - organization\n27\t---\n28\t\n29\t# Move push_branch to its own submodule with colocated tests\n30\t\n31\t## Summary\n32\t\n33\tExtract the `push_branch` builtin function from `builtins/__init__.py` into `src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch.py`. Create a colocated `push_branch_test.py` with unit tests. This is one of the simplest builtins — no private helpers, just a `git push -u origin` call.\n34\t\n35\t## Requirements\n36\t\n37\t1. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch.py` containing the `push_branch` function decorated with `@builtin(\"push_branch\")`.\n38\t2. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch_test.py` with unit tests covering: dry-run path, successful push.\n39\t3. Remove `push_branch` from `builtins/__init__.py`.\n40\t4. Add submodule import in `__init__.py` to trigger registration.\n41\t5. All existing tests pass.\n42\t\n43\t## Technical Approach\n44\t\n45\t### `src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch.py`\n46\t\n47\t```python\n48\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n49\timport subprocess\n50\tfrom darkfactory.builtins._registry import builtin\n51\tfrom darkfactory.workflow import ExecutionContext\n52\t\n53\t@builtin(\"push_branch\")\n54\tdef push_branch(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None: ...\n55\t```\n56\t\n57\t### `src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch_test.py`\n58\t\n59\t- Dry-run logs the push command without subprocess calls\n60\t- Successful push calls `git push -u origin {branch}`\n61\t\n62\t## Acceptance Criteria\n63\t\n64\t- [ ] AC-1: `src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch.py` contains the `push_branch` function.\n65\t- [ ] AC-2: `push_branch_test.py` covers dry-run and successful push.\n66\t- [ ] AC-3: `push_branch` is no longer defined in `builtins/__init__.py`.\n67\t- [ ] AC-4: `from darkfactory.builtins import push_branch` still works.\n68\t- [ ] AC-5: All tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n69\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1f534906-900d-426c-84f5-c086d3be4bd4","uuid":"53f57835-5068-41f8-9134-e85c580e3045","timestamp":"2026-04-09T03:20:24.294Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/prds/PRD-549.6-move-push-branch.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-549.6\"\ntitle: \"Move push_branch to its own submodule with colocated tests\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: xs\ncapability: trivial\nparent: \"[[PRD-549-builtins-package-split]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-549.1-pytest-config-wheel-conftest]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-549.2-scaffold-builtins-package]]\"\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-549.12-final-cleanup]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch.py\n  - src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch_test.py\n  - src/darkfactory/builtins/__init__.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - refactor\n  - tests\n  - organization\n---\n\n# Move push_branch to its own submodule with colocated tests\n\n## Summary\n\nExtract the `push_branch` builtin function from `builtins/__init__.py` into `src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch.py`. Create a colocated `push_branch_test.py` with unit tests. This is one of the simplest builtins — no private helpers, just a `git push -u origin` call.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch.py` containing the `push_branch` function decorated with `@builtin(\"push_branch\")`.\n2. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch_test.py` with unit tests covering: dry-run path, successful push.\n3. Remove `push_branch` from `builtins/__init__.py`.\n4. Add submodule import in `__init__.py` to trigger registration.\n5. All existing tests pass.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch.py`\n\n```python\nfrom __future__ import annotations\nimport subprocess\nfrom darkfactory.builtins._registry import builtin\nfrom darkfactory.workflow import ExecutionContext\n\n@builtin(\"push_branch\")\ndef push_branch(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### `src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch_test.py`\n\n- Dry-run logs the push command without subprocess calls\n- Successful push calls `git push -u origin {branch}`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `src/darkfactory/builtins/push_branch.py` contains the `push_branch` function.\n- [ ] AC-2: `push_branch_test.py` covers dry-run and successful push.\n- [ ] AC-3: `push_branch` is no longer defined in `builtins/__init__.py`.\n- [ ] AC-4: `from darkfactory.builtins import push_branch` still works.\n- [ ] AC-5: All tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n","numLines":69,"startLine":1,"totalLines":69}}}
